23
00:02:01,230 --> 00:02:04,760
Sentaro...

24
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:12,040
Tsugumi, what's wrong?

25
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,940
Oh, no, it's nothing.

26
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:18,170
I'd like these.

27
00:02:18,170 --> 00:02:23,170
"Rain of Remorse"

28
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:44,830
Man, sorry about last night.

29
00:02:44,830 --> 00:02:47,630
I didn't have time to call...

30
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:49,790
...and I ended up drinking
until morning.

31
00:03:03,510 --> 00:03:05,950
There's...no breakfast, right?

32
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:07,280
Then, we can go downstairs...

33
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:16,760
Thanks for the food.

34
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:21,130
Go like you're supposed
to this year, okay?

35
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:22,790
What're you talking about?

36
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,300
Never mind!

37
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:28,860
I'll go by myself!

38
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:47,450
"Ogawa"

39
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,090
Coming!

40
00:03:57,770 --> 00:04:00,570
Welcome, Tsugumi!

41
00:04:00,570 --> 00:04:02,230
We've been waiting for you.

42
00:04:03,540 --> 00:04:05,200
Is Hajime...

43
00:04:18,260 --> 00:04:19,950
Tsugumi bought this?

44
00:04:21,060 --> 00:04:22,990
A photographic collection?

45
00:04:22,990 --> 00:04:24,500
Something this expensive...

46
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,860
"Japan's Cherry Blossoms"

47
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:35,860
"Photographed at Mutsumi Village"

48
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:59,750
A-Ai, you have another message.

49
00:05:05,970 --> 00:05:08,870
Moody, isn't she?

50
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:11,310
Doesn't it sort of make
you feel uneasy?

51
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:40,540
It makes me realize...

52
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:43,510
I guess it's already been
that long since Ayumi died.

53
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,980
Yes, it has.

54
00:05:44,980 --> 00:05:48,910
After all, Tsugumi was so
little back then, but now...

55
00:05:48,910 --> 00:05:53,180
Look. She made this beautiful
dish of rice with chestnuts.

56
00:05:54,850 --> 00:05:58,260
Isn't today the anniversary
of your wife's death?

57
00:05:58,260 --> 00:06:00,160
The wife I split up with.

58
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,790
But why are you asking that?

59
00:06:02,790 --> 00:06:04,560
Tsugumi came by yesterday,

60
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:08,670
asking about how to make
rice with chestnuts.

61
00:06:08,670 --> 00:06:11,940
Because it was her
mother's favorite dish.

62
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:13,970
I didn't know...

63
00:06:13,970 --> 00:06:16,670
You guys knew each other since
you were students, right?

64
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:18,670
And you even had a kid...

65
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:22,940
It was one of those so-called
youthful indiscretions.

66
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:28,050
The report on the faculty meeting
is the next issue's special feature!

67
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:32,290
Who the hell backs down without a fight
just because you got turned away?!

68
00:06:32,290 --> 00:06:34,790
I heard Shibata got shot down.

69
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:35,090
-Hey, you sure you guys
aren't getting soft?!

70
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:37,800
-So that's why he's so pissy.
-Hey, you sure you guys
aren't getting soft?!

71
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:40,360
So who shot him down?
What's she like?

72
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,600
-Miss Ogawa,
-A journalist takes a stand for
the reader's right to know!

73
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,170
-A quiet girl who used to be the same...
-A journalist takes a stand for
the reader's right to know!

74
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:46,000
...language class until last year.
-A journalist takes a stand for
the reader's right to know!

75
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,990
Do you get that?!

76
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:53,510
M-Miss Ayumi Ogawa,
please go out with me!

77
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:59,580
Her personality is the total
opposite of Shibata,

78
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:02,150
but it was love at first
sight for Shibata...

79
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:05,280
...and he expressed the feelings he's
had these past two years today, but...

80
00:07:15,370 --> 00:07:18,930
If you've got time for idle
chitchat, go check the copy!

81
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:22,340
You better keep me company
until morning tonight.

82
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:23,310
We know.

83
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,640
Shibata...

84
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,810
Yes!

85
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:46,960
About what happened earlier...

86
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,200
Yes!

87
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,530
I'm sorry.

88
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:52,400
Not at all.

89
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:57,570
I mean, being confronted like that
so suddenly in front of everyone...

90
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:00,540
I'm sorry!

91
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,740
I hadn't thought about that.

92
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:09,050
I'll never show my face
around you again. I promise.

93
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:14,360
Oh, um, that's not it.

94
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,850
What?

95
00:08:21,670 --> 00:08:24,630
That is...if you would have me...

96
00:08:29,370 --> 00:08:32,210
Of course! It's totally okay!

97
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:44,790
I never expected Shibata would be
the first of us to get married.

98
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:47,420
Surprising...but I guess, not really.

99
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:50,420
He fell head over heels for Ayumi,
after all.

100
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,870
Hello?

101
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:57,200
What? Really?

102
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:04,640
Has something happened?

103
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,540
The Tokyo Public Prosecutors
went in...

104
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:08,550
...to former Prime Minister
Takenoshita's private residence.

105
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:10,270
It looks like this
is going to be big.

106
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:15,020
I'll go, too.

107
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:16,010
Sorry!

108
00:09:27,730 --> 00:09:31,290
Maybe that was the first
stroke of bad luck for us...

109
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:48,010
Noriko Hayashi.

110
00:09:49,420 --> 00:09:53,980
"Central Hotel 7"

111
00:09:54,830 --> 00:09:57,730
Central Hotel 7...

112
00:09:57,730 --> 00:10:00,700
Tsugumi? Tsugumi?

113
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:04,130
Are you okay, Tsugumi?

114
00:10:04,130 --> 00:10:07,340
Oh, yeah, I'm okay.

115
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:10,140
But you look pale.

116
00:10:10,140 --> 00:10:12,200
Maybe we should go take
a little break.

117
00:10:15,810 --> 00:10:18,710
Hell Girl's notified me again.

118
00:10:20,050 --> 00:10:23,690
This time, I know both
the place and the name.

119
00:10:23,690 --> 00:10:26,210
"Cafe New Deen"

120
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:36,200
If I tell Hajime, he's sure
to get in Hell Girl's way.

121
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:36,900
"Address List / Hajime /
Grandpa / Grandma / Yuko"
