to get in Hell Girl's way.

122
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,000
"Address List / Hajime /
Grandpa / Grandma / Yuko"
But...

123
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,000
"Address List / Hajime /
Grandpa / Grandma / Yuko"
Maybe he'll understand that
Hell Girl is doing the right thing.

124
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,200
Maybe he'll understand that
Hell Girl is doing the right thing.

125
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:48,010
Are you not feeling well, after all?

126
00:10:48,010 --> 00:10:49,610
What?

127
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:51,980
You don't seem to have much
of an appetite, either.

128
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:54,250
Oh, th-that's not true.

129
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:02,160
Tsugumi?

130
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,150
I'm going to go make a call.

131
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:10,330
"Answer
...Tsugumi"

132
00:11:10,930 --> 00:11:13,100
It's Tsugumi.

133
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:15,710
You'd better apologize properly.

134
00:11:15,710 --> 00:11:18,910
It's never quite
as easy as that...

135
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:20,240
Hello?

136
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:23,380
Noriko Hayashi.
Central Hotel 7.

137
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:24,540
What?

138
00:11:27,350 --> 00:11:29,340
Was it Hell Girl, Tsugumi?

139
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,660
H-Hey!

140
00:11:32,660 --> 00:11:33,990
Put it on my tab!

141
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:40,930
So anyway, Noriko's bored
of the current condo.

142
00:11:40,930 --> 00:11:44,000
And it doesn't have a good view, either.

143
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,840
All right, all right. I'll buy you one.

144
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:50,510
Honestly, you sure are spoiled, woman.

145
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:54,840
But that's because I can
always depend on you, Keiichi.

146
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:58,580
Central Hotel 7?

147
00:11:58,580 --> 00:12:01,220
Please hurry!
It's an emergency!

148
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:02,590
Sure, sure.

149
00:12:02,590 --> 00:12:06,720
But you know,
my motto is safe driving.

150
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,230
The fastest you can manage is fine.

151
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:09,720
Sure, sure.

152
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:16,060
"Central Hotel 7"

153
00:12:25,810 --> 00:12:28,000
Oh, dear, we're stuck
in a traffic jam. See?

154
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:32,050
Are you with the media?

155
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:33,550
Something like that.

156
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:35,320
I knew it.

157
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:38,960
I've only been driving
a taxi for half a year,

158
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:41,860
but I can always spot
the media people.

159
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:43,190
Is that right?

160
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:45,160
Charging around late at night
and early in the morning.

161
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:48,100
No time to pay
attention to family.

162
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:50,870
That's the kind of vibe
they give off.

163
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:53,200
I bet you've got some
troubles at home, too, right?

164
00:13:00,210 --> 00:13:01,470
Hello?

165
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:06,980
I understand. I'll be right there.

166
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:08,750
You're going out?

167
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:11,860
There's apparently been an
accident at some power plant.

168
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:13,460
I'll call you when
I know what's going on.

169
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:14,830
Oh, you can stay in bed.

170
00:13:14,830 --> 00:13:15,990
Look after the house
while I'm gone.

171
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,920
"I'll be back by 7.
I'll call."

172
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:13,120
When she's born...

173
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:15,110
Maybe things will change a little...

174
00:14:17,350 --> 00:14:22,060
Even after Tsugumi was born,
Hajime didn't change, did he?

175
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:24,960
Not only that,
but now that he had a child,

176
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:28,330
he threw himself into his
work even more than before.

177
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:35,270
I wonder how Ayumi must have felt...

178
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:36,600
Sorry to keep you waiting.

179
00:14:37,770 --> 00:14:39,680
What's wrong?

180
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:42,010
I-It's nothing.

181
00:14:42,010 --> 00:14:43,480
Then, shall we go?

182
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:46,620
Central Hotel 7.

183
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:48,610
Oh, that's it there.

184
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:51,720
Are you going to stake it out?

185
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,050
I don't know.

186
00:14:55,660 --> 00:14:56,990
That day...

187
00:14:56,990 --> 00:15:00,160
As usual, I hadn't returned
home in days,

188
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:02,130
continuing a stakeout...

189
00:15:06,140 --> 00:15:08,840
It was because it was rumored that a
politician popular for his integrity...

190
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:11,810
...was having a torrid affair.

191
00:15:13,810 --> 00:15:15,140
But...

192
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,390
H-Hold on, Shibata!
What's wrong?!

193
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:32,330
Please let me go, Mr. Murai!

194
00:15:35,770 --> 00:15:37,760
Hey, wait, Shibata!

195
00:15:44,410 --> 00:15:45,740
Who're you?

196
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:50,380
You bastard!

197
00:15:50,380 --> 00:15:53,080
You bastard! You bastard!
You bastard! You bastard!

198
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:55,420
Stop this, Shibata! Hey, quit it!

199
00:15:57,890 --> 00:16:00,190
The wife of the man pursuing a story
about an extramarital affair...

200
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:02,460
...turned out to be having
an affair herself.

201
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:04,430
It wasn't even funny.

202
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:07,290
Oh, Sir, your receipt!

203
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:15,870
"Central Hotel 7"

204
00:16:15,870 --> 00:16:17,440
"Central Hotel 7"
Noriko!

205
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:17,960
Noriko!

206
00:16:19,140 --> 00:16:20,970
Don't do it!

207
00:16:22,810 --> 00:16:24,480
Your grievance has been heard.

208
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,820
"Central Hotel 7"
Your grievance has been heard.

209
00:16:25,820 --> 00:16:27,510
"Central Hotel 7"

210
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:34,580
Ai, I'll leave your
under-kimono here.

211
00:16:49,170 --> 00:16:52,310
Do you know what
it is that you've done?!

212
00:16:52,310 --> 00:16:54,850
You've sent a person to Hell!

213
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:57,580
I loved her...

214
00:16:57,580 --> 00:16:59,350
But to her, I was nothing but...

215
00:16:59,350 --> 00:17:04,150
No, all men were nothing
but deep pockets to her.

216
00:17:04,150 --> 00:17:06,850
How could I forgive
a woman like that?!

217
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:10,890
How could I forgive her?!

218
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:15,230
While I was working,

219
00:17:15,230 --> 00:17:16,830
she was fooling around
with other men!

220
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:19,040
You saw her, too, Mr. Murai!

221
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:22,370
Not to mention leaving Tsugumi
alone while she was out!

222
00:17:22,370 --> 00:17:25,780
But think about Tsugumi.

223
00:17:25,780 --> 00:17:28,110
She still needs a mother.

224
00:17:28,110 --> 00:17:30,680
She does not need a mother
who is unfaithful!

225
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:32,320
Shibata...

226
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:35,120
I'm the one suffering
the most here!

227
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:37,350
She's been the only one
for me since college!

228
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:42,790
If this was what she was
going to put me through...

229
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:45,330
I wish I'd never met her.

230
00:17:45,330 --> 00:17:49,830
So I wanted her
to be gone for good...

231
00:17:49,830 --> 00:17:52,830
That it served her right
to go to Hell...

232
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:04,610
What is this? What's going on?!

233
00:18:06,950 --> 00:18:09,120
H-Hey, you there!

234
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:11,120
You called?

235
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:13,020
My friend just suddenly...

236
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:15,260
...turn into money or something?

237
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:16,690
What?

238
00:18:16,690 --> 00:18:19,160
How splendid for you.

239
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:21,600
To you, men are...

240
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,500
...money, right?

241
00:18:26,570 --> 00:18:27,730
Nooo!

242
00:18:35,610 --> 00:18:38,880
You there! Please help me!

243
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:40,850
Money, is it?

244
00:18:40,850 --> 00:18:43,320
If 5 yen will do...

245
00:18:47,020 --> 00:18:49,960
What is this?!
What's going on?!

246
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:54,460
What a stupid thing to do...

247
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:56,660
What do you know?

248
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:08,810
Hajime...

249
00:19:08,810 --> 00:19:10,780
What're you doing here?

250
00:19:13,650 --> 00:19:15,890
I want to start over.

251
00:19:15,890 --> 00:19:18,820
How can I trust someone who's
already betrayed me once?!

252
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,760
Is there no way?

253
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:26,830
No.

254
00:19:26,830 --> 00:19:29,160
And I have no intention of
letting you see Tsugumi, either.

255
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:33,070
Go on.

256
00:19:33,070 --> 00:19:34,730
Don't show up around here again.

257
00:20:05,570 --> 00:20:06,900
It can't be...

258
00:20:11,370 --> 00:20:12,710
